Join in the largest LIVE group breathing session on Instagram on Sunday, May 3rd. Getting together from all around the world, united by the power of our breath. Can't wait to see you all X

00:00 - Amsterdam (May 3)
08:00 - Sydney (May 3)
15:00 - Los Angeles (May 2)
18:00 - New York (May 2)

Program:
5min. - Welcoming everyone
15min. - Guided breathing
5min - Hof music

#iceman #wimhof #live #breathwork #groupbreathing #instalive #guidedbreathing #wimhofmethod #justbreathe #power #breathe #livemusic

node.text:
3 rounds of Wim Hof breathing, gradually building up.

Please keep in mind;
- Don't do the breathing exercises in a swimming pool, before going underwater, beneath the shower or piloting any vehicle, without proper supervision. - Always practice in a safe environment. Sitting or lying on the ground/couch
- Do the exercises without force and gradually build up.  Best on Empty stomach.

Download the free “Wim Hof Method” in the Appstore or Google Play for more in-depth explanations and interactive breathing exercises.

Everyone's been asking what do I think about the Coronavirus, and here it is. It's a serious matter that must not be taken too lightly. But you have the power to make a change. It is important for everyone to know how significant their individual actions are especially in such a delicate time. We need to protect ourselves, our loved ones and those in more vulnerable situations. The healthiest things you can do now is to: - wash your hands frequently - avoid touching your face
- keep social distancing - avoid coming into contact with people at risk (people over 70 and/or immunocompromised)
- don't travel unless it's extremely urgent
- avoid large public gatherings
- if you've been coughing repeatedly or you're having a fever seek medical attention and follow the directions of your local health authority
- even if you don't have symptoms you probably already know it doesn't mean you don't have the virus, so it's important to follow all the other health guidelines above in order to not further spread the virus.

In 2014 Radboud University had proven that through the WHM you can upregulate your immunity, by increasing the amount of white blood cells and B-lymphocyte cells. These cells form the army in your body that fight off micro-organisms and viruses that don’t belong there. At the same time, the WHM helps a person better influence the innate immune response resulting in lowering the severity of symptoms such as fever or headache. Overall, less inflammation and disease-like symptoms.

This study showed that you can boost your immune system through the method. The Wim Hof Method therefore could prove to be a useful tool in fighting against unwanted guests in your body by speeding the development of immunity and reducing symptoms.

I suggest you start with practicing the method and get your army ready.

Stay safe everyone. Sending you all a big hug from a distance. All the love and all the power to you. X

node.text:
Did you know that not all of our CO2 emissions go straight into our atmosphere? Instead, forests from all around the world are protecting us from even faster rates of climate change by absorbing CO2 🌳

But forests don't do this alone; they have a little magic help from mushrooms. Particularly, it seems that certain types of root fungi have a crucial influence on the forest's ability to absorb CO2 at impressively high rates 🍄

Unfortunately, human development has also left a bad mark on this. With increasing use of nitrogen in some parts of the world, these root fungi are in danger. It is crucial to put an end to nitrogen pollution in order to save these carbon-protecting fungi, and in turn help saving the planet 🌍

#mushroom #fungi #forests #co2 #environment #mothernature #lovenature #mycelium #fungilove #fantasticfungi #savetheplanet #protectnature #noplanetb #pollution #pollutionfree #mycology

node.text:
This penguin colony has fallen by 77% 🐧

Chinstrap penguins [swipe to see them] are one of the most abundant species of penguins in Antarctica. Sadly, many of their colonies have been plummeting in the last 50 years. This shows that something has drastically changed in the marine ecology. 

Unfortunately, chinstraps aren't the only ones affected. If environmental change continues at its current rate, more than 80% of emperor penguin colonies are in danger of becoming almost extinct. By 2100, the number of adults may be insufficient to
ensure continuation of this species.

🌎 Share this post to spread awareness

#savethepenguins #chinstrap #emperor #penguins #naturelover #savetheocean #wildlife #environment #naturelove #conservation #biodiversity #wimhofmethod

If you find yourself uneasy or stressed by certain situations, it's important to harness habits that help you regain your calm. Here's a simple Wim Hof Method Meditation exercise you can try out anytime you need to find your inner peace:

1. Sit down in a safe, comfortable place and clear your mind.
2. Start connecting to your breath. Let yourself breathe naturally.
3. Start counting your breaths. Each inhale and exhale is one count. Count your breaths up to 7, and then from 7 back to 1. If you find yourself suddenly thinking about your daily life and your to-do list, return to counting the breaths. You will eventually find yourself able to just count the breaths, up to 7 and back down again. 

The blood flow will go into the deeper areas of your brain, awakening feeling, not thoughts. Let the feeling become stronger. Follow the feeling and go as deep as you want. As you go along, the counting will fade away, like a song fading out. Follow the feeling and go deep into yourself, deep into peace. 

👉Save this post for later so you may use this exercise whenever you need to and share with someone that might also find it useful
